programme.title: Hex Vs Witchcraft
programme.desc: Yu Nan (Yi Lei) is a compulsive gambler. He makes his wife as a down payment for his debt, feeling regretted and decides to kill himself but stops when a beautiful ghost appears.

programme.title: The Human Goddess
programme.desc: This is a love story between an alluring fairy, Seventh Sister, who comes down from heaven to experience life in 70's Hong Kong, and a man who is running a debt laden orphanage.

programme.title: Lady With A Sword
programme.desc: A young woman tries to find a group of villains responsible for her eldest sister's death, but is shocked to discover that her fiancé is one of them.

programme.title: The Snake Prince
programme.desc: Ti Lung who lives on the Snake Mountain of Kwangsi with his brothers the Black Snake and the Yellow Snake, have been trying to turn into humans for a thousand years.

programme.title: Disco Bumpkins
programme.desc: George Lam Tsz-Cheung tries, along with his buddies Hamburger and Snoopy, to find love and success in the world of TV commercials.

programme.title: The Happy Trio
programme.desc: Li Ching, the best actress of her era, play Ah Chiao is a girl from a rural village stranded in the city, who befriends a kind-hearted transient and a retired actor.

programme.title: The Merry Wife
programme.desc: Li Ching, a 17-year-old girl who marries her 35-year-old teacher. Comedy ensues when Li decides to go to the same school with her husband but attempting to hide their relationship.

programme.title: Fast Fingers
programme.desc: After his release from prison, Uncle Bill returns to make a fortune with his past thieving partners. They continue to prey on the unsuspecting public, but are closely watched by the upright police chief.

programme.title: The 82 Tenants
programme.desc: This story happens in an antiquated compound with various types of tenants. A properties developer contended to acquire the properties for redevelopment.

programme.title: Operation Lipstick
programme.desc: A professor's assistant stole a micro-film storing the secret of a newly invented nuclear reactor and sells it to a crime syndicate. However, it's fall into the hands of a nightclub dancer and a thief.

programme.title: Sons Of Good Earth
programme.desc: An award winning movie for best script and best editing. Another tale of a Sino-Japanese war that artistically and emotional triumphed, it clearly portrays the life of wartime.

programme.title: Brothers Five
programme.desc: A young woman sets out to reunite feuding brothers to take out a gang of killers who have murdered their father.

programme.title: The Vengeful Beauty
programme.desc: The Flying Guillotine assassins are secretly working for the Emperor and its leader Jin is sent to kill Hon, who knows this secret. Hon’s pregnant wife Rong seeks to kill Jin but retreats to protect her unborn child.

programme.title: Dirty Ho
programme.desc: Master Wang, who is actually the 11th prince, poses as an antique connoisseur to hide his true identity. When he meets Dirty Ho, a witty con artist, Wang knows he has found the right man to help him.

programme.title: The Silver Fox
programme.desc: Lily Ho portrays the feared swordswoman Silver Fox, who witnessed her father senselessly wounded and her mother raped. 18 years later it's payback time.

programme.title: The Silver Fox
programme.desc: Lily Ho portrays the feared swordswoman Silver Fox, who witnessed her father senselessly wounded and her mother raped. 18 years later it's payback time.

programme.title: Twin Blades Of Doom
programme.desc: A retired martial artist is forced back into action after his family is murdered by the evil Ghost Gang. Without friends, he is forced to ally himself with a quintet of killers.

programme.title: The Golden Seal
programme.desc: A family film about a young couple and their son, living in the Aleutian islands and cut off from the world. Like the Aleut natives, the father has long pursued the golden seal, a near-mythical creature.

programme.title: Shaolin Mantis
programme.desc: The Emperor orders Feng to find proofs of Master Tian’s rebellion in his house. Feng falls in love with Tian’s granddaughter and marries her.

programme.title: Temple Of The Red Lotus
programme.desc: A young kid heads off to Dragon Valley to meet the childhood friend who was promised as his bride. When he gets there, he finds that the family of the bride might not be an entirely honest bunch of people though.

programme.title: Hong Kong 73
programme.desc: Back in 1973 the stock market was skyrocketing, but HK's social issues continued to worsen. TVB and Shaw Bros' biggest stars come together for this ingenious tongue-in-cheek tale.

programme.title: Death Valley
programme.desc: A hired killer unknowingly makes friends with the man he's been sent to assassinate.

programme.title: The Adulteress
programme.desc: In the waning day of the Ching Dynasty, the son of the local magistrate murdered a peddler and raped his wife. The wife had been framed for her husband's murder by the rapist.

programme.title: The Battle Wizard
programme.desc: Dali Prince Tuan Yu knows nothing about martial arts, but leaves the palace for the martial arts world. He meets a snake sorceress and his mysterious half-sister.

programme.title: The Butterfly Chalice
programme.desc: Action maestro Chang Cheh tells the story of Chin Feng, who meets the beautiful Ting Hung while on the run for accidentally killing an arrogant bully.

programme.title: The Fighting Fool
programme.desc: It's Meng Yuan-wen versus Kuan Feng in this wild and wacky wushu saga of a priceless pole with a spectacular secret.

programme.title: Godfather Of Canton
programme.desc: A commissioner is arrested by envoy Cheng for corruption with an unintentional helped of Lin. Working for Cheng, Lin soon learns how to get dockside bribes spin-off from Chang.

programme.title: The Dragon Missile
programme.desc: Sima works for a corrupt lord Qin who is suffering from a deadly disease that only a special herb can cure. He sends him on an urgent mission to retrieve it and fight with his ultimate weapon, the Dragon Missile!

programme.title: The Bride Napping
programme.desc: A rich girl Yue Ying, together with her maid Chun Lan, encounter a poor scholar Bian Ji at a fete. Chun Lan realizes Yue Ying is in love with him, but mixes his identity with a bandit due to an old servant's confusion.

programme.title: Three Sinners
programme.desc: Based on the classic Ming Dynasty novel The Water Margin, Three Sinners is a Huangmei Opera about love, betrayal, murder, and redemption.

programme.title: Two Tigers
programme.desc: Two Tigers is a crime comedy movie about a bumbling young man Fang Nan, who kidnaps a middle-aged businessman, Zhang Cheng Gong, for ransom.

programme.title: My Kickass Wife
programme.desc: Jade is a beautiful royal guard who is set up for marriage by the Queen in order to avoid the King setting eyes on her. Jade falls for Sean and helps him win the contest for her. After the wedding, Sean discovers her bad temper and visits a brothel in his despair. He meets and is attracted to a girl there, not knowing she has a secret agenda...

programme.title: Septet: The Story Of Hong Kong
programme.desc: Seven of Hong Kong's most revered directors, all with distinctly unique styles, come together for the first time to compose a symphony of stories for their city from the 50s to the future.

programme.title: One More Chance
programme.desc: Water's ex-girlfriend asked him to take care of their autistic son. As Water lives with his son, he discovers his son's talent in running, Water decides to give up his dissipated life and support his son's dream.

programme.title: Black Ransom
programme.desc: Mann is forced to return to his former glory when he is assigned to investigate a former police inspector suspected to be kidnapping mafia bosses and demanding ransoms in exchange for their lives.

programme.title: The Movie Emperor
programme.desc: Actor Lau Wai-Chi has a huge following of devoted followers and is always keeping an eye on his rivals. After accepting to play the lead in a modest indie drama, Lau begins the laborious process of mastering the acting skills for the role.

programme.title: Wolf Hiding
programme.desc: A cold-blooded killer, Chen An vows to take revenge for her sister who was killed by a crime gang. Dealing with the police and the triad at the same time, a final battle between good and evil has just begun!

programme.title: Fallen Angels
programme.desc: The funkier cousin to Chungking Express, director Wong Kar Wai looks at five fallen angels who suffer love and loss amidst the crime and chaos of Hong Kong's neon nights.

programme.title: The Way We Keep Dancing
programme.desc: This sequel of 'The Way We Dance' features the plight of Hong Kong's grassroots performing artists as they fight against the government's plan to gentrify an industrial district where they settled in.

programme.title: Echoes Of The Thunder
programme.desc: Two half-brothers, Nam and Fire, are top racing drivers. In a racing challenge with Japanese driver Kenji, Fire is seriously injured and depressed. So, Nam decides to compete with Kenji in an illegal street car race.

programme.title: Where The Wind Blows
programme.desc: Detectives Lui Lok and Nam Kong build a corruption system that creates conflicts between the triad and the police. When ICAC hunts down the two, their control finally comes to an end.

programme.title: Sex And The Beauties
programme.desc: It is said that Hong Kong is a sexy and sexual city where life is breathtakingly fast but glamorous. Fear of marriage, single & successful psychiatrist, Selina and other beauties seek for love and happy endings.

programme.title: City Of Desire
programme.desc: Sandra returns to Macau after having been in Canada for the last twenty years. Her father is ill and the business is being passed on to her, but she is taken aback to discover that the family business is prostitution.

programme.title: Night And Fog
programme.desc: Following “The Way We Are”, this is based on a true story happening in Tin Shui Wai. It revolves around an older, unemployed Hong Kong man, his young Mainland wife and their two daughters. Their lives, unfortunately, are anything but easy, and the shocking conclusion raises issues about the plight of the socially deprived lower class.

programme.title: Initial D
programme.desc: For five years, 18-year-old Takumi delivers tofu in his fathers near-obsolete Toyota AE86 every morning and because of that, he has become a good racer and also unwillingly perfected the art of drifting.

programme.title: The White Storm 3: Heaven Or...
programme.desc: An undercover cop who invade a drug cartel led by a notorious Thai drug lord. In classic heroic bloodshed fashion, the two develop a bond of brotherhood.

programme.title: Ashes Of Time Redux
programme.desc: After his beloved woman married his brother, Ou Yang Feng moves to the desert to run an inn and becomes a killer agent. He makes acquaintance of different people with their different stories.

programme.title: You Are The One
programme.desc: A talented rogue trader experiences a 180-degree change in life when he encounters a girl who does not believe good things will happen to her. Will they fall in love?

programme.title: Call Me Agent
programme.desc: One day, Miu Ling rescues an injured secret agent who promises to make her his apprentice. From then on, her life is turned upside down and she goes onto a roller-coaster of madcap adventures.

programme.title: Knight Of Shadows: Yin & Yang
programme.desc: Pu Song Ling, a legendary demon hunter, is asked to investigate a case involving missing teenage village girls with Constable Yan Fei and accidentally discover a mysterious love between a knight and a female ghost.

programme.title: Winner Takes All
programme.desc: Two private detectives want to gain fame by solving a series of robberies. However, they were fooled by the King of Thieves during the investigation. It was later discovered that all the robberies were related to a Japanese businessman, Miyamoto.

programme.title: Cliff Walkers
programme.desc: This film follows four Communist Party special agents who embark on a secret operation in the Japanese puppet state of Manchukuo in 1932.

programme.title: In The Mood For Love
programme.desc: In the Mood for Love' is Wong Kar-Wai's most acclaimed feature, navigating the subtle love relationship between Chow Mo Wan and Su Li Zhen after both discover their spouses are having an affair.

programme.title: Kill Switch
programme.desc: A pilot battles to save his family and the planet after an experiment for unlimited energy goes wrong.

programme.title: 73 Questions With G. Rodriguez
programme.desc: Actress Gina Rodriguez invites Vogue into her room at The Jeremy West Hollywood and answers 73 questions. In this episode, presented by the Google Assistant, Gina talks about the premiere of her new movie "Ferdinand," managing her busy schedule, and the causes most important to her.

programme.title: 24 Hours With A$Ap Ferg
programme.desc: A$AP Ferg says he is inspired by his hometown neighborhood of Harlem, and it’s not hard to see why. See what 24 hours in the rapper’s life looks like, from getting a pedicure at his favorite local nail salon to popping wheelies on the corner.

programme.title: Gold
programme.desc: In the not too distant future, a drifter travelling through the desert discovers the largest gold nugget ever found. He must guard it from thieves amid harsh conditions and wild dogs while waiting for his partner to return.

programme.title: 73 Questions With Emily Blunt
programme.desc: While Anna Wintour is abroad, Emily Blunt fills her shoes and takes charge at the Vogue office while answering 73 questions. As Emily fulfills her duties as Vogue's Editor-in-Chief, she talks about the pizza in New York City, becoming Mary Poppins, and what she's learned about fashion from her movie roles.

programme.title: 24 Hours With Katy Perry
programme.desc: How did Katy Perry, the ultimate California girl, transform into an avant-garde fashion siren for the Met Gala? This behind-the-scenes video gives a glimpse at everything it took to go from private jet to after-party, including her gala performance of “Bon Appétit” with Migos.

programme.title: Labor Pains
programme.desc: A young woman pretends to be pregnant in order to avoid being fired from her job. When that gets her special treatment by everyone involved in her life, she tries to keep up the lie for nine months.

programme.title: 73 Questions With Hailey Bieber
programme.desc: While model Hailey Bieber gets ready to shoot her Vogue cover, she answers 73 intriguing questions. Hailey talks about planning her wedding with Justin Bieber, her desire to learn the Shake Shack secret sauce recipe, and (almost!) shows us how to open up a beer with your teeth.

programme.title: Platinum
programme.desc: A mysterious man arrives in Houston and gets the opportunity of a lifetime when a pretty hooker with considerable business acumen teaches him the pimp game.

programme.title: Killing Season
programme.desc: Two veterans of the Bosnian War, one American, one Serbian, find their unlikely friendship tested when one of them reveals their true intentions.
